00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.000
Install and configure SQL Server 2012 which is required to install SharePoint 2013. You can also use the steps to install SQL Server 2008 R2 SP1 which are exactly the same.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:23.000
The video is part of a series of 6 videos describing the SharePoint 2013 installation process.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:37.000
I'm going to install SharePoint using 2 virtual machines: A Domain Controller and a Server used to install SQL Server 2012 and SharePoint 2013.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Start the SQL Server installation media and select a new SQL Server standalone installation.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:22.000
Accept the license agreement.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:39.000
Wait until the setup support files have been installed.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:48.000
Select the SQL Server feature installation.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Select at least the Database Service Engine and the Managment Tools Basic.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Add additional features depending on your needs.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Keep the default instance.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:45.000
Review disk space requirements and proceed.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:03:04.000
Add the SQL Server Service Account and enter the password.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Keep the collation settings.

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:46.000
Specify SQL Server administrators.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:04:00.000
In a devlopment environment use the local administrator and SharePoint Setup Administrator.

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:43.000
Start the SQL Server 2012 installation.

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:18.000
Assign the dbowner and securityadmin roles to the SharePoint Setup Administrator.

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:36.000
Open SQL Server Management Studio and go to security and logins.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:48.000
Verify that the SharePoint Setup Administrator has dbowner and securityadmin roles.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:06:08.000
The sysadmin role is only assigned since I use the same account to manage SQL Server inside my development environment.

